        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} a quick check (wow - only 60 horsepower!), we got the keys and quickly packed our things in the room. I checked the Teide website - and darn, no more tickets available for today. So we spontaneously replanned and booked for tomorrow instead. </p>
        <p> Today we wanted to visit the steep cliffs of Los Gigantes and then head to Masca - we had discovered this place through WDR's "Wunderschön" with Tamina Kallert and really wanted to go there, especially to the "Alte Schule" restaurant. </p>
        <p> We had barely started driving when the weaknesses of our small rental car became apparent - with only 60 horsepower, you're really at a disadvantage in these mountains. But hope dies last. Our first stop was a viewpoint above Los Gigantes - wonderful view with cool drinks. </p>
        <p> Then we went down into the town. We strolled around a bit, watched fish in the harbor basin, and took some nice pictures of the impressive cliffs from the small beach. We looked around at the restaurants and considered whether we might want to do a boat tour from here in the coming days. </p>

